Iéna with an I would make sense because the d' indicates that a world beginning with a vowel would follow, so L and J are out. Otherwise, it would be &quot;de&quot;

I'd also say that this was taken from the Eiffel Tower, probably the first level. (Too low to be from the top, which is where the photograph you linked to, @slecorne, was taken)

Also, the reason it looks different is that this photo shows the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palais_de_Chaillot">old Palais du Trocadéro</a>; a newer building, the Palais de Chaillot, was built in 1937 and still stands today.
